column24: In the second half of the study, pressing the mouse didn't move onto the next screen i.e. asking you to say "yes" or "no". There would be a long wait between the sentence and the next screen. Initally, I thought that the experiment was broken or laggy.  Occasionally, pressing the mouse did work so I would say about 90% of the time I had to wait until the experiment moved to the next screen instead of clicking.
